JOHANNESBURG - Alleged assassination plotter Elvis Ramosebudi will know on Monday if he will be granted bail.Ramosebudi has been charged with incitement to murder.READ: NPA has no evidence of coup-plotting against RamosebudiHe was arrested by the Hawks nearly two weeks ago on suspicion that he had been planning to assassinate President Jacob Zuma and other prominent South Africans.The State has argued that Ramosebudi had a well-constructed plan for his plot.But the defence says the 33-year old unemployed father is not a repeat offender and doesn't pose a threat to himself or others.eNCA